Abuse Amazon KMS to Decrypt Protected Data
Objectives
By the end of this lab, students will be able to:

Identify common Amazon KMS misconfigurations and security vulnerabilities
Analyze KMS key policies for overly permissive access controls
Develop Python scripts to interact with KMS using boto3
Detect sensitive information in decrypted data using pattern matching
Implement security best practices for KMS key management
Prerequisites
Basic understanding of AWS IAM and encryption concepts
Python programming fundamentals
Familiarity with JSON and AWS policy structure
Linux command line experience
