Troubleshooting Tips
Issue: boto3 import errors

Solution: Verify Python 3.8+ is active: python3 --version
Install boto3 if needed: pip3 install boto3
Issue: AWS credential errors in simulation

Solution: Confirm ~/.aws/credentials and ~/.aws/config exist with correct format
Check file permissions: chmod 600 ~/.aws/credentials
Issue: Regex patterns not matching expected data

Solution: Test patterns individually using Python interactive shell
Use re.IGNORECASE flag for case-insensitive matching
Verify input data format matches pattern expectations
Conclusion
This lab demonstrated critical KMS security vulnerabilities arising from misconfigured key policies. You learned to identify overly permissive access controls, automate decryption attempts, and analyze decrypted data for sensitive information. Key takeaways include:

Always implement least-privilege access with specific principals and actions
Use condition statements to restrict access by IP, service, or MFA requirements
Regularly audit KMS key policies and CloudTrail logs for unauthorized access
Separate encryption keys by data sensitivity and use case
Enable automatic key rotation for customer-managed keys
Apply these principles to secure KMS implementations in production environments and prevent unauthorized data access.
